# Link to Specific Sections

When adding markdown links to other pages in the book, ALWAYS link to the specific section heading, not just the page.

```markdown
❌ BAD — links to the page but not the relevant section:
[dehumanization](./types-of-mistakes.md)
[Narrative Lock](./invisible-patterns.md)

✅ GOOD — links to the exact section:
[dehumanization](./types-of-mistakes.md#a-note-on-the-word-predator)
[Narrative Lock](./invisible-patterns.md#narrative-lock)
```

Before adding a link, search for the actual heading text in the target file to get the correct anchor. Do not guess anchor names — verify them.
